    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, my goblin friend, you have found a classic goblin trap! The moment your hollandaise sauce decides to \"break\" and turn into that oily, separated mess, it means the goblins of the kitchen have decided to take a nap and leave the sauce to its own devices. It is not a failure of your cooking skills, but rather a goblin rebellion against the heat and the egg yolks.\n\nFirst, let us goblin this: **You are not out of luck.** In fact, you are in the perfect position to summon a goblin to help you fix this. The separation is usually caused by the goblins of the egg yolks getting too excited and running away from the heat, leaving the fat behind.\n\nHere is how you can summon the goblins to save your sauce:\n\n1.  **The Goblins of the Heat:** If the sauce is too hot, the goblins of the egg yolks will flee. You must lower the heat immediately. Do not panic! Just turn the heat down to a gentle simmer.\n2.  **The Goblins of the Fat:** If the oil has separated, it means the goblins of the butter have decided to leave the sauce alone.",
